@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Linko' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other
files or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?


  To play, click on a tile occupied either by the star or a small
square. If it is located on a tile that is linked to the empty
tile, that object will move there. Clicking on a link will 'switch'
it to its alternate position, linking to another tile. Note that
the 'starting' tile from where a link is connected will always
remain the same.

  Some tiles may be located in spaces next to each other diagonally,
but if they are not connected by a link, no object can go from one
of those tiles to the other... besides, the game would be too easy!

  The fewest moves you make to get to the exit, the better. As each
move of an object from one tile to another, or link switch count as
a move.

  When you complete a game board, Linko displays a new board and
the game continues...

  You can restart the current game board anytime, by clicking on
the 'Restart' button, or by using the Right-Amiga and 'R' key
combination.

  Have fun!

@endnode

